<h2>Step 5 - Disable Control Q &amp; Control S</h2>

<p>Edit your .bashrc file which is found in your home directory, if you cannot find it - create it. Add the following line. In some terminals Control Q and Control S keys are already assigned by the operating system. These two combinations are made use of by rtorrent so we have to make sure they are disabled before we use rtorrent in an interactive session.</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>stty -ixon</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

